      • createInstallation

        public void createInstallation(java.lang.String deviceToken,
                               java.util.ArrayList<java.lang.String> installationChannels,
                               com.raweng.built.BuiltResultCallBack callback)
        Create a new installation.
        Parameters:
        deviceToken - Registration token which user received from google server for GCM.
        installationChannels - channels subscribe to. Channels can have the values below: 
         For list of supported channel please check push channels.

 You can add custom channels as well.
        callback - BuiltResultCallBack object to notify the application when the request has completed.

        Example :
         // 'blt5d4sample2633b' is a dummy Application API key
 BuiltInstallation installation = Built.application(context, "blt5d4sample2633b").installation();

 ArrayList<String> installationChannels = new ArrayList<String>();
 installationChannels.add("Sports");
 installationChannels.add("Technology");

 installation.createInstallation("your_device_token", installationChannels, new BuiltResultCallBack() {
      @Override
      public void onCompletion(BuiltResponseType responseType, BuiltError builtError) {

      }
 });
